The Windows version of hyp2mat is cross-compiled on linux using MXE.
See http://www.mxe.cc

Before compiling, in the mxe root, type 
make gcc gtk2
to install dependencies.

Copy hyp2mat.mk into MXE src/ directory
Update hash keys using
make update-checksum-hyp2mat
or use
openssl sha1 pkg/hyp2mat-0.0.14.tar.gz 
and update src/hyp2mat.mk manually.

Cross-compile hyp2mat for win32 by typing 
make hyp2mat
in the mxe root.

Package the win32 release using the following commands, run from the mxe root:
mkdir hyp2mat
(cd ./usr/i686-pc-mingw32/share/hyp2mat/ ; tar cvf - . ) | ( cd hyp2mat; tar xvpf - )
cp -p ./usr/i686-pc-mingw32/bin/hyp2mat.exe ./hyp2mat/
zip -9 -r hyp2mat-win32-current.zip ./hyp2mat
# not truncated
